FT  05 DEC 94 / Company News (This Week): Compass - Other companies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The acquisitive catering and healthcare group, is expected on Thursday to
announce profits of Pounds 57m for the year to the end of September, sharply
ahead of the previous Pounds 41.5m. The rise has been driven by
acquisitions, the biggest of which is Canteen Corporation, the third largest
US caterer. It was bought in June for Dollars 450m, and is likely to
contribute about Pounds 7m this time. While underlying growth is seen as
steady, this year's rail strike is thought to have cost the group's station
catering business about Pounds 1m.
