delivering an object lesson in the hazards of decorating letterheads with
trophy names. When one William Colby applied for his Vietnamese visa, the
powers that be had not forgotten the former head of the CIA, who had spent
most of his war in Vietnam, orchestrating efforts to overthrow the Hanoi
regime of the day.
The application was politely rejected - demonstrating that the country's
enthusiasm for US investment dollars clearly has its limits.
