FT  05 DEC 94 / Business Travel: Train accidents
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
No passengers or staff were killed in UK train accidents in the 12 months to
March 31 - for the first time since 1985.
But the number of collisions between passenger trains doubled, according to
the Health and Safety Executive. There were also increases in the number of
collisions between trains in stations, accidents at level crossings, and
vandalism.
The number of 'significant train accidents' rose from 133 to 142.
