<HEADLINE>
FT  05 DEC 94 / Olympics drug abuse 'shock'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TONY WALKER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BEIJING
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
China's Olympic Committee expressed 'deep shock and regret' at the weekend
over a finding by the Olympic Committee of Asia that 11 Chinese athletes had
tested positive for performance enhancing drugs at the recent Asian games in
Hiroshima. China announced that it had appointed a committee to investigate
the episode and said those involved would be punished severely under
international rules. The report was carried by People's Daily in its
back-page 'brief news' columns. The OCA finding that a number of its top
athletes, including several members of its all-conquering women's swimming
squad, had failed doping tests is proving a severe embarrassment for China.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>CNZ  China, Asia.
