<HEADLINE>
FT  03 DEC 94 / Weekend Money (Budget Analysis): Your budget
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Income tax: No change in 20p, 25p or 40p rates. From next April, 20p lower
band extended by Pounds 200 to Pounds 3,200. Personal allowance indexed (to
Pounds 3,525); threshold for higher rate tax increases to Pounds 24,300.
Age-related allowances increase above inflation. Personal allowance for
those aged 65-74 will rise to Pounds 4,630, 75 and over to Pounds 4,800.
Married couple's allowance*: Relief to be restricted to 15 per cent (from 20
per cent). But married couple's age allowance will rise for those aged 65-74
to Pounds 2,995 and for those aged 75 and over to Pounds 3,035. Income limit
for age-related allowances will increase to Pounds 14,600; all from next
year.
VAT-on-fuel* compensation package: Help package to cuahion effects of
increase of VAT on fuel - from 8 per cent to 17.5 per cent from April 1 - to
be extended. Home Energy Efficiency Scheme basket of grants increases by
Pounds 10m. Cold-weather payments rise to Pounds 8.50 per week from Pounds 6
two years ago. Single pensioners will receive Pounds 52 more in their
retirement pensions while couples will receive Pounds 73 beginning 1995-96.
From April 1996 there will be Pounds 68 extra on the single pensioner rate
and Pounds 96 for pensioner couples.
National insurance: Employers will earn an NI 'holiday' of up to a year by
taking on people unemployed for two years or more, from April 1996.
Capital gains tax: Exempt amount increased from Pounds 5,800 to Pounds 6,000
a year and inheritance tax threshold increased from Pounds 150,000 to Pounds
154,000, both from April 6 1995.
Tobacco and alcohol: Tax on a packet of 20 cigarettes to be increased by
10p. No change in the level of duties on beer, table wine and spirits.
Fuel and vehicle taxes: Petrol taxes up immediately by 2.5p a litre for
leaded and unleaded petrol. Tax on diesel up 3p a litre. Vehicle excise duty
on cars will rise by Pounds 5 to Pounds 135.
Miras*: Tax relief on mortgage interest on first Pounds 30,000 of mortgage
cut from 20 per cent to 15 per cent from next April.
Housing benefit: Rules to be changed so cost of benefit will not be
reimbursed to local authorities for rents that are significantly higher than
local averages.
Business taxation: No change to Advance Corporation Tax, Corporation Tax or
Capital Allowances. Recovery of VAt to be allowed on business lease car
purchases.
Small business support: Threshold for business VAT registration to be
increased to Pounds 46,000. Thirty per cent increase in threshold for
monthly PAYE payments for businesses, taking in two-thirds of all
businesses.
Business rates: Rises as a result of revaluation limited to 10 per cent for
large businesses/buildings and 7.5 per cent for small ones.
Tax avoidance: Measures to tighten some loopholes, including avoidance of
VAT through property transactions and share issues, or operations with
discounted securities.
* Scheduled in previous budget.
