FT  03 DEC 94 / London Stock Exchange: GMet up on broker support
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Food and drinks group Grand Metropolitan rose 3 to 381p as the group's
brokers lent their support. Full-year figures on Thursday had received a
mixed reaction but buyers returned yesterday encouraged by recommendations
from Panmure Gordon and NatWest Securities.
Panmure pointed out that the shares were at a five-year low and analysts at
the broker said: 'This discount to the average market rating must be
unsustainable.'
The team at NatWest Securities urged investors to 'add' to holdings and
said: 'The shares look fairly rated for 1995, at a small discount to the
market for a year in which we forecast a small decline in earnings.
Thereafter, growth should start to accelerate.' Dealers also reported
switching into GrandMet from Guinness, which fell 7 to 445p.
