<HEADLINE>
FT  03 DEC 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The market was quiet this week, reports Man Producten. Prices for black and
white were under pressure, as buying interest vanished temporarily. The
black pepper price decrease was mainly caused by selling pressure from
Brazil and India. Brazilian exporters were forced to sell some material to
pay interest on loans. Indian traders felt able to sell off remaining stocks
as their new crop will become available in January. This new crop is
expected to be the same or slightly better than the last one. Muntok white
was quoted at USDollars 3,600 a tonne, spot, and for December/January
shipment at Dollars 3,500, cif. Spot black pepper faq was at Dollars 2,450
and for December/January shipment at Dollars 2,400, cif.
</TEXT>
